<div class="text-center">
    <h3 class="display-2">Navigating the OWASP Top Ten Vulnerability Demonstration Application</h3>

    <p style="text-align:justify">
        TWelcome to the "OWASP Top Ten Vulnerability Demonstration" application. This guide will help you navigate through the application to understand the implemented vulnerabilities and their mitigations.
        The application showcases both vulnerable and secure implementations for each of the OWASP Top Ten vulnerabilities, providing a comprehensive learning experience.
    </p>

</div>
<div>
    <h5>Overview of the Application</h5>
    <p>
        The application is a contact manager where users can:
        <ul>
            <li>Register and log in</li>
            <li>Create, view, edit, and delete contacts</li>
        </ul>
        Each contact includes a name, description, and creation date, associated with a specific user.
    </p>
    <h5>Application Architecture</h5>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>Frontend: Razor Pages for user interface</li>
            <li>Backend: ASP.NET Core with Entity Framework Core for data handling and business logic</li>
            <li>Database: SQL Server for data storage</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <h5>Navigating the Vulnerabilities</h5>
    <p>

        <ul>
            <li>A01:2021 – Broken Access Control</li>
            <ul>
                <li>Backend: ASP.NET Core with Entity Framework Core for data handling and business logic</li>
                <li>Database: SQL Server for data storage</li>
            </ul>

        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>A02:2021 – Cryptographic Failures</li>
            <p>Controller: CryptographicFailuresController</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Explore insecure cryptographic practices and their secure alternatives.</li>
                <li>Understand the importance of using strong cryptographic algorithms and proper key management.</li>
            </ul>

        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>A03:2021 – Injection</li>
            <p>Controller: InjectionController</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Review examples of SQL injection and other types of injection attacks.</li>
                <li>Compare vulnerable code with secure coding practices that use parameterized queries and ORM features.</li>
            </ul>

        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>A04:2021 – Insecure Design</li>
            <p>Controller: InsecureDesignController</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Identify insecure design patterns and how they can be avoided.</li>
                <li>Understand the principles of secure software design.</li>
            </ul>

        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>A05:2021 – Security Misconfiguration</li>
            <p>File: SecurityMisconfiguration.cs</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Discover common security misconfigurations that can leave applications vulnerable.</li>
                <li>See how to configure your application securely to mitigate these risks.</li>
            </ul>

        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>A06:2021 – Vulnerable and Outdated Components</li>
            <p>File: VulnerableAndOutdatedComponents.cs</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Understand the risks of using outdated and vulnerable components in your application.</li>
                <li>Learn best practices for keeping your dependencies up-to-date and secure.</li>
            </ul>

        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>A07:2021 – Identification and Authentication Failures</li>
            <p>Controller: IdentificationAndAuthenticationFailuresController</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Learn about common authentication issues, such as weak passwords and improper session management.</li>
                <li>See how to implement secure authentication mechanisms.</li>
            </ul>

        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>A08:2021 – Software and Data Integrity Failures</li>
            <p>Controller: SoftwareAndDataIntegrityFailuresController</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Explore vulnerabilities related to software and data integrity, such as insecure deserialization.</li>
                <li>Implement measures to ensure data integrity and secure software updates.</li>
            </ul>

        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>A09:2021 – Security Logging and Monitoring Failures</li>
            <p>Controller: SecurityLoggingAndMonitoringFailuresController</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Recognize the importance of proper logging and monitoring for security.</li>
                <li>Learn how to implement effective logging and monitoring to detect and respond to security incidents.</li>
            </ul>

        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li>A10:2021 – Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)</li>
            <p>Controller: SSRFController</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Understand SSRF attacks and their potential impact.</li>
                <li>Learn how to validate and sanitize input to prevent SSRF vulnerabilities.</li>
            </ul>

        </ul>
    </p>
</div>
